The paper deals with physical-layer security in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper proposes several beamforming schemes for improving the secrecy rate of wireless transmissions. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
